Comment (src/views/dashboard/partials/SuggestionScopeDialog.vue:151):
**[High] Cost estimate over-reports badly — it ignores server-side chunking; wire it to the new preview endpoint.** This computes `plannedCalls` as a raw cartesian product (`controls.length × labelSetHashes.length`), but the server batches work via chunking — `PlannedCalls = ceil(controls / MaxControlsPerChunk) × ceil(labelSets / MaxLabelSetsPerChunk)` (api: internal/service/relational/suggestions/core.go). The chunk sizes are server-only (not in `/config`), so the dialog can't compute the real number locally. Result today: a scope of 16 controls × 89 label-sets shows **1424 AI calls** when the actual cost is **~1**, which both scares users off and trips the `warningThreshold = 25` large-run gate for runs that are actually tiny.

API PR 420 now exposes a dedicated preview endpoint for exactly this — use it instead of the local product:

- **`POST /api/oscal/system-security-plans/{id}/dashboard-suggestions/preview`** (handler `Preview`, auth-gated). It resolves the scope and returns the planned call count **without** creating runs or enqueueing work.
- **Request body** (optional; same shape as generate, only `scope` is used): `{ "scope": { "controlKeys": string[], "labelSetHashes": string[] } }`. Empty/no body = global (all controls × all label-sets) — which lines up with this dialog's existing `selectedScope()` that omits arrays when 'All' is selected.
- **Response**: `{ data: { plannedCalls: number, controlCount: number, labelSetCount: number } }` — `plannedCalls` is the real chunked count; `controlCount`/`labelSetCount` are the **resolved** counts. Returns **422** when the resolved scope is empty.

Suggested change: add `buildPreviewDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint(sspId)` in dashboard-suggestions.ts (mirroring `buildGenerateDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint`), call it (debounced) whenever the selected scope changes, and drive the warning/info copy (the two `{{ plannedCalls }} AI calls covering … controls x … label-sets` blocks) from `data.plannedCalls` + `data.controlCount`/`data.labelSetCount` rather than local lengths. Also reconsider the hardcoded `warningThreshold = 25` — base the large-run confirmation on the server's real `plannedCalls` (or a server-provided threshold), and handle the 422 'empty scope' case for the preview the same way generate does.
Implementation guidance: In src/views/dashboard/partials/dashboard-suggestions.ts, add and export buildPreviewDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint(sspId: string) returning `/api/oscal/system-security-plans/${sspId}/dashboard-suggestions/preview`, mirroring buildGenerateDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint. In src/views/dashboard/partials/SuggestionScopeDialog.vue, stop computing plannedCalls from selectedControls.length * selectedLabelSetHashes.length for the user-facing estimate and large-run gate. Add a debounced preview request that posts `{ scope: selectedScope() }` to the preview endpoint whenever selectedControls or selectedLabelSetHashes changes, using the same omission semantics as generate so all-selected dimensions are omitted from scope. Store preview plannedCalls, controlCount, and labelSetCount from `response.data.data`; drive both estimate/warning text blocks and canGenerate/largeRun confirmation from preview.plannedCalls and the resolved counts. Keep the existing `warningThreshold = 25` unless a threshold is actually returned by the API; the important change is that the threshold compares against the server-returned plannedCalls, not the local cartesian product. Handle preview 422 for empty resolved scope by showing the same blocking ceiling/scope error style used for generate 422 and preventing generate until the operator changes scope. Guard against stale preview responses after rapid selection changes, debounce the request to avoid a POST per click, and fall back to a loading/unknown estimate state rather than showing the old inflated local estimate while preview is pending. Add or update tests for a large local cartesian scope where preview returns plannedCalls below 25, verifying no large-run confirmation is required and the rendered copy uses preview controlCount/labelSetCount.
